Input:
   KB = {set of propositional sentences}
   α  = query sentence

Output:
   True  → if KB entails α
   False → otherwise

Steps:

1. Collect all propositional symbols that appear in KB or α.

2. Generate all possible combinations of truth values (True/False)
   for these symbols (i.e., all possible models).

3. For each model:
      a. Evaluate whether KB is True in this model.
      b. Evaluate whether α is True in this model.
     
      If KB is True and α is False in any model:
           → Return False  (KB does NOT entail α)

4. If no such model is found:
      → Return True  (KB ENTAILS α)
